Task: Create DefinitionCard component

Summary:
Implemented a card component for vocabulary terms that displays the term prominently with its definition and optional related terms. The component follows the e-textbook design system with proper typography, spacing, and accessibility.

Files Created:
- components/textbook/DefinitionCard.tsx (28 lines)
- __tests__/components/textbook/DefinitionCard.test.tsx (181 lines)

Files Modified:
- components/textbook/index.ts (added DefinitionCard export)

Implementation Details:
- Props: term (required), definition (required), relatedTerms (optional, array of strings)
- Visual: Card-like appearance with rounded border, subtle shadow, proper padding and margins
- Structure: article element with h3 heading containing strong element for term
- Typography: font-display (Lora) for term, proper line heights for definition
- Related Terms: Optional section with border separator, bulleted list below definition
- Accessibility: Proper heading structure (h3), semantic article element, proper list structure

Test Coverage (18 tests):
- Basic rendering (term prominence, definition, no related terms)
- Related terms (renders when provided, list structure, single term, empty array)
- Visual styling (card appearance, typography, spacing)
- Accessibility (heading structure, article element, list structure)
- Edge cases (empty definition, multiline definition, long term, many related terms, special characters)

All tests passing, lint passing, typecheck passing.

Why:
DefinitionCard is essential for the vocabulary-focused sections of the e-textbook. Students need clear, visually distinct presentation of key terms with their definitions and connections to related concepts. This component provides a consistent, accessible way to present vocabulary throughout the curriculum.
